<a href="javascript:card_browser(90)">Relics of Moria</a> x2    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> The Shire is not happy. Orcs have come on through the Misty Mountains to disrupt their life and the Hobbits are livid with rage. Hobbit Farmers throw away their stakes and find a new use for their pitchforks. Farmer Maggot proves to be a f*ggot with a pitchfork. Bilbo Consorts With Wizards for tactics as the entire Shire population follows behind Frodo, Sam, Merry, Pippin and some Southerner called Boromir who proves to be really good at blowing his Horn, or making others blow it instead. Frying Pans fly and Hobbit Swords stab, THE SHIRE WANTS REVENGE!<br>
<br>
This is a Fun deck meta-ed against Isengard Orcs, Sauron Orcs and Moria Orcs i.e. the three least-used shadow cultures so respect it. Don&#39;t try playing against Uruks or Nazgul. I haven&#39;t tried, and maybe will never dare.<br>
<br>
Basically, a variation of the Hobbit-burn deck-type. Get the first Farmer early, and from then on, your Hobbits all play for free (except Bilbo who will be free after a 2nd Farmer). Once you spot your Site 3 with Silinde&#39;s help, you will even get card-draws for dumping allies on the table. Trust me, this deck burns like a b*tch with allies on Free Peoples and Moria on shadow. 86 is not a problem.<br>
<br>
Get the Horn ASAP. Then for your Frying Pans and Hobbit Swords, if you feel like a serious boring Joe, play them on your companions. But NO, give Bilbo a Sword (overwhelm-prevention) and all your allies their FRYING PANS! Get the Horn out! The Orcs come? CHARGE!!!<br>
<br>
Use your allies and their Frying Pans to whack your opponent&#39;s Moria Orcs or Sauron Orcs silly. Whack whack whack THWACK. For those Isengard Orcs, they are big enough to kill you, but WHO CARES? Let the Farmer give that Retainer a big whack in the privates before it gets killed off. Bounder helps a lot if you don&#39;t feel like whacking. WHACK WHACK WHACK. You use denial tactics like Bill, No Stranger, A Talent, Consorting and the fact that almost everything plays for free for denial to limit Orcs then WHACK everything else your opponent plays. Farmer Maggot and Bilbo are key. They have 3 vitality i.e. THEY CAN WHACK TWICE!! And if your opponent plays Moria? Hohoho...THREE MONSTROUS TROLLS!!! Don&#39;t even suggest to me you don&#39;t have the Hobbit allies to exert.<br>
<br>
Oh gosh darnit! The Hobbits went too far into the Misty Mountains. It appears that something is awakening...DURIN&#39;S BANE. IT&#39;s the FLAME OF UDUN! RUN!!!<br>
<br>
But suddenly Bilbo with a Sword and +3 from Horn stands before the cookie monster. He Consorts with the Wizards and Bounder and the Balrog swings his whip...Bilbo didn&#39;t feel anything. The &#39;rog tries again and Bilbo gives the finger.<br>
<br>
For shadow, since this is a fun deck, Moria with a twist. GOBLIN SPEARMEN! Use them with Spears obviously. Flankers with Axe, Spears with Spearmen...just like every Moria swarm deck.<br>
<br>
You know, if you add Such a Little Thing to the Moria half, the Free Peoples and Shadow will be totally equipped to fight and hate each other. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=24963"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=24963" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
